{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"695077ea-0cc8-4a9a-b537-02931e963196","content":"Use `dotnet watch` to re-run tests automatically on every file save:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis watches for file changes and re-runs the filtered test automatically.\n\n**About the failing test:** `RemoveStock` never throws — it just subtracts, allowing negative stock. You'll need to add a guard, e.g.:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException($\"Cannot remove {quantity} from {sku} (available: {current})\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply that fix and start `dotnet watch` so you can iterate?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a7546b1-5a38-4b19-af40-8b23a1eab131","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for rapid test iteration. This project uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (as configured in global.json) with MSTest. The `dotnet test --watch` or `dotnet watch test` command would work for this.\n\nLet me explain how to set it up and also note the bug in the code (RemoveStock doesn't throw when quantity exceeds available).","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"CFDD:2D7BDE:14A7517:181DE87:69EC18C7"},"id":"e417465a-7969-4560-989d-5b41dca236ae","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:28:47.004Z","parentId":"d1e6e7e8-68b1-40d3-92e2-8f3f7c0a78a8"}
